		<div>As for hardware firewall solutions... I was over at Best Buy here in Southern California, they have a Linksys unit, it's a wireless access point, 4 port switch with a router in it, so you can do NAT and basic hardware firewalling for $70.  I bought this when it was new for $250, so prices have really come down.  Here is the outpost.com listing for it:<br />
<br />
<a href="http://shop4.outpost.com/product/2957055" target="_blank">http://shop4.outpost.com/product/2957055</a><br />
<br />
With this unit, I have the added bonus of being able to peruse erollisimarr.com from the bathroom.<br />
<br />
Which brings me to Wireless Access Points and securing them.  I will try to come up with a writeup about best practices for that as well and will share when I get it done.</div>
